    "note": "Core product-usage health — 'is the loop working?' Acquisition, activation, the clean→export north-star, surface mix, catalog-gap quality, the custom-parameter IAP-calibration funnel, history, and the review gate. Durable across phases. v3 (2026-06-23): removed the broken 'Surface mix' insight (was order 7) — it was a multi-aggregation `timeseries` line chart, a shape the imported-insight renderer plots as a single series, so it read empty even with data underneath. The per-event breakdown in insight 6 ('exports per day by event', a `groupBy` over `type`) already conveys the same surface mix and renders; insight orders intentionally skip 7. REWRITTEN for the shipped 1.1.0 taxonomy (v2, 2026-06-16): the dead `Action.Markdown.succeeded` event is gone (the Markdown extension folded into Copy-as-you-want → `Action.Format.succeeded`), and the north-star export set now spans ALL five surfaces. The 1.1 new-surface, growth-loop, AI-advisor and engine-depth insights live in the companion Dashboard-LinkClean-Growth-Surfaces.json; the IAP funnel in Dashboard-LinkClean-Monetization.json (both now LIVE, not dark). Import-only via the TelemetryDeck UI; the JSON is the source of truth. NORTH-STAR EXPORT SET (a clean *delivered*, deduped per distinct output): Home.URL.copied + Home.URL.shared (app) · Action.Clean.succeeded (Clean ext) · Action.Format.succeeded (Copy-format ext) · Intent.Clean.succeeded (App Intents — the clipboard/return IS the delivery) · QR.Result.actioned + QR.Code.generated (QR). Deliberately EXCLUDED: Home.URL.cleaned and QR.Scan.succeeded are *cleans*, not exports (curiosity until acted on); History.Entry.actioned is a re-export of a past clean (tracked separately, insight 23, to avoid double-counting). DAU/installs read TelemetryDeck's built-in signals — verify the exact `type` strings in your instance (renamed in the SDK 2.0 'Grand Rename'). Every signal also carries two default parameters: `tier` (free/pro) and `surface` (app/action/copyAction/intent) — slice any insight by `tier` for the Pro-vs-free behavioral read. Companion KPI doc: docs/strategy/kpis.md (⚠️ predates 1.1 — this dashboard set is the live taxonomy; see docs/dashboards/README.md).",
